<title>REPUBLIC OF IRELAND: Independent shareholders approve W&amp;H bid.</title>
<headline>Independent shareholders approve W&amp;H bid.</headline>
<dateline>DUBLIN 1996-10-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>Independent Newspapers Plc said shareholders approved the company's offer to acquire the entire issued share capital of Wilson and Horton at an extraordinary meeting held on Friday.</p>
<p>On September 16, Independent announced it was offering NZ$10.50 per share for the New Zealand group. It already holds a 22.6 percent interest with the same amount in the hands of family trusts linked to Independent Chairman Tony O'Reilly.</p>
<p>At a separate extraordinary meeting, shareholders also approved a number of amendments to the articles of association of the company, Independent said in a statement.</p>
